Description: Head and shoulders bust right, wearing headcloth, with legend in two parts broken by the king's head, in one circle. (obverse)
Greek cross in a circle, solid with flared equal length arms, in one outer circle. (reverse)
State: Associated with: Aksumite Kingdom Africa: Aksumite Kingdom

Bibliographic references: BMCAK / Catalogue of the Aksumite Coins in the British Museum (91, p.33)
